From today's NYTimes:
 
 http://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/28/us/28martin.html?_r=1&oref=slogin
 
 "Del Martin, Lesbian Activist, Dies at 87
 
 "Del Martin, who married her partner of 55 years, Phyllis Lyon, on June 16 in the first legal gay union in California and who helped found the pioneering lesbian-rights group the Daughters of Bilitis, died Wednesday in San Francisco. She was 87...."

My heart goes out to her partner. But I am happy that she was finally able to get married; celebrating her love in (what she believed was) the ultimate way. Both Martin and Lyon has done a lot for the LGBT community and I commend them for doing it during a time that was a lot more intolerant than now.
